definition.value: A trihydroxyflavone with the hydroxy groups at positions C-5, -6 and -7.
A trimethoxyflavone that is the 5,6,7-trimethyl ether derivative of baicalein. It has been isolated from the plant Callicarpa japonica and has been shown to exhibit antiviral activity.
A hydroxy monocarboxylic acid anion that is acetate where the methyl group has been hydroxylated.
A C4-dicarboxylate that is the E-isomer of but-2-enedioate(2-)
A tricarboxylic acid trianion that is the conjugate base of glycyrrhizinic acid.
The glycosyloxyflavone which is the 7-O-glucuronide of baicalein. It is an active ingredient of Chinese herbal medicine Scutellaria baicalensis.
A nitrile oxide resulting from the oxidation of hydrogen cyanide.
